	How to write, compile, debug and run C programs on Linux
	========================================================

There are some prompts below, but you should add anything else you think
will be useful.

Useful sources of information
=============================
google
http://www.cplusplus.com/reference/cstdio/putc/

Writing C programs
==================
The language is a lower level than java and requires more care when working 
with the constructs because there are not as many safety nets at runtime

Compiling C programs
====================
you can use the gcc program to compile and link the program
optinally you can create a makefile and save your programs compile command
configuraton there

Linking C programs
==================
this is done with the ld command, however the gcc program can do this 

Running C programs
==================
as normal program ( no "java Class" )

Comparing output from C and Java programs
=========================================
the precision of the two devisions is different


